claim.claim-text:
1. A method for monitoring a self-contained server rack system, comprising:
discovering, by at least one hardware processor, the self-contained server rack system containing a plurality of equipment as being connected within a data center;
discovering, by at least one hardware processor, the plurality of equipment within the self-contained server rack system, wherein the plurality of equipment is automatically discovered in response to connecting the self-contained server rack system to a single mounting point in the data center, and wherein the mounting point includes a single connector that connects all of the plurality of equipment in the self-contained server rack system;
configuring, by at least one hardware processor, the self-contained server rack system;
configuring, by at least one hardware processor, the plurality of equipment within the self-contained server rack system;
monitoring, by at least one hardware processor, the self-contained server rack system and the plurality of equipment for changes in operational status; and
configuring a cooling apparatus associated with the self-contained server rack system, wherein the cooling apparatus provides cooling to the self-contained server rack system based on a power consumption of the plurality of equipment contained in the self-contained server rack system.

8. A non-transitory computer-readable medium comprising computer-readable instructions executed by a processor to implement a method for monitoring a self-contained server rack system, the method comprising:
discovering the self-contained server rack system containing a plurality of equipment as being connected within a data center;
discovering the plurality of equipment within the self-contained server rack system, wherein the plurality of equipment is automatically discovered in response to connecting the self-contained server rack system to a single mounting point in the data center;
configuring the self-contained server rack system, and wherein the mounting point includes a single connector that connects all of the plurality of equipment in the self-contained server rack system;
configuring the plurality of equipment within the self-contained server rack system;
monitoring the self-contained server rack system and the plurality of equipment for changes in operational status; and
configuring a cooling apparatus associated with the self-contained server rack system, wherein the cooling apparatus provides cooling to the self-contained server rack system based on a power consumption of the plurality of equipment contained in the self-contained server rack system.

15. A system for monitoring a self-contained server rack system using a non-transitory computer-readable medium encoded with computer-readable instructions, the computer-readable instructions comprising instructions stored thereon that are executed by a processor, the system comprising:
at least one subsystem to discover the self-contained server rack system containing a plurality of equipment as being connected within a data center;
at least one subsystem to discover the plurality of equipment within the self-contained server rack system, wherein the plurality of equipment is automatically discovered in response to connecting the self-contained server rack system to a single mounting point in the data center, and wherein the mounting point includes a single connector that connects all of the plurality of equipment in the self-contained server rack system;
at least one subsystem to configure the self-contained server rack system;
at least one subsystem to configure the plurality of equipment within the self-contained server rack system;
at least one subsystem to monitor the self-contained server rack system and the plurality of equipment for changes in operational status; and
at least one subsystem to configure a cooling apparatus associated with the self-contained server rack system, wherein the cooling apparatus provides cooling to the self-contained server rack system based on a power consumption of the plurality of equipment contained in the self-contained server rack system.
